title: The Mystery of a Turkish Bath
creator: E. M. Gollan (Rita)
description: LibriVox recording of The Mystery of a Turkish Bath, by Rita. Read by Darvinia. A group of guests, at an exclusive luxury hotel in Hampshire, are the witnesses of an illustration of occult powers, demonstrated by “the Mystery”, as Mrs. Jefferson named the beautiful stranger who one day appeared in the Turkish Baths of the hotel. The events that follow lead Mrs. Jefferson to question the wisdom of her interest in the occult. (Summary by Bev. J. Stevens) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; mystery; occult; tragedy; ghost stories
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
